  "text": "HomeCareersLearn how the brand goes from product ideation to development to market at a rapid, industry-disrupting pace.Steph here. I'm so excited to share that I'll be joining Colette Laxton and Mark Curry, co-founders of skin-care brand The Inkey List, on The Fashionista Network. But here's the best part: I want you to join me! It's your opportunity to interact live with us, ask questions and be a part of the show.Laxton and Curry co-founded The Inkey List in the U.K. in 2018, based on the belief that \"better knowledge powers better decisions.\" The brand's mission is to simplify skin care, break down complicated beauty jargon and promote empowerment among its community. Since that initial launch, The Inkey List has expanded into 32 countries via a retail partnership with Sephora.Laxton's career has spanned marketing, branding and product development, while Curry's began as a microbiologist-virologist, with a stint as a school teacher before making the jump into the beauty business. The pair met while working for British beauty industry giant Boots and eventually decided to venture out and create their own brand.Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesDuring our live show, the duo will offer a glimpse at how The Inkey List goes from product ideation to development to market at a rapid, industry-disrupting pace; we'll discuss the current state of the beauty business and the product(s) they're most excited about right now.This conversation will be publicly accessible (no paywall!) on The Fashionista Network, powered by interactive media platform Fireside, and you'll get the chance to participate and join the stage with video to ask questions directly. Learn more about The Fashionista Network here.You don't want to miss this show on Tuesday, April 29Â at 1:00 p.m. ET/10:00 a.m. PT. Sign up for free access now (and don't forget to become a member to access all of our members-only shows and perks as well).From emerging startups to Fortune 500 companies, brands are building awareness, driving sales and gaining followers by partnering with Fashionista. Discover our unique digital offerings here.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
